article.headline: Wisconsin-Milwaukee routs Judson (ILL) 89-56
article.story: MILWAUKEE -- Kyle Kelm and Austin Arians both scored 14 points and the University of Wisconsin-Milwaukee thrashed NAIA member Judson (ILL) 89-56 on Tuesday night. The Milwaukee bench accounted for 68 points as the Panthers played everyone on the roster in the lopsided victory. J.J. Panoske added 10 points and grabbed eight rebounds and JeVon Lyle scored 10. Matt Tiby, who leads the team, averaging 15.3 points per game, took on a different role, shooting only 3 times but dishing out six assists in just 15 minutes of play. Milwaukee led 54-28 at the half and never trailed in the game. They shot 52 percent as a team and out-rebounded Judson 46-29. Judson committed 16 turnovers compared to the Panthers seven. The Panthers led by as much as 37 points with a few minutes remaining. Drew Makiewicz led all scorers putting in 17 points for the Judson Eagles.
